    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-08-10T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-08-10T08:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <head>113. Telegram From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD3" type="from"
                        >Rusk</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d113fn0">Source: Department of State,
                        Presidential Correspondence: Lot 66 D 204. Confidential; Priority; Eyes
                        Only.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Bonn</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-08-10T14:00:00+01:00">August 10, 1963, 2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Secto 55. Personal for the President from the Secretary. No other distribution.
                    Just before my departure Chairman <persName corresp="#p_KNS2"
                        >Khrushchev</persName> telephoned from Sochi and asked me to convey his
                    personal distress and his condolences to you and
                        Mrs.<persName>Kennedy</persName>.<note n="1" xml:id="d113fn1">A son born to
                        the Kennedys on August 7 died 2 days after his birth.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD3">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
